{
  "video_id": "iiIdQFSUx2k",
  "title": "The Giver, Chapter 1 Audiobook",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 620.0,
      "end_time": 2449.0,
      "text": "The Giver, chapter 1."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2449.0,
      "end_time": 5040.0,
      "text": "It was almost December, and Jonas was beginning to be"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 5040.0,
      "end_time": 6040.0,
      "text": "frightened."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 6040.0,
      "end_time": 7040.0,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 7040.0,
      "end_time": 8040.0,
      "text": "Wrong word, Jonas thought."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 8039.999999999999,
      "end_time": 9040.0,
      "text": "Frightened meant that deep, sickening feeling of something"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 9040.0,
      "end_time": 10969.0,
      "text": "terrible about to happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 10969.0,
      "end_time": 12670.0,
      "text": "Frightened was the way he had felt a year ago when an"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 12670.0,
      "end_time": 15860.0,
      "text": "unidentified aircraft had overflown the community twice."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 15860.0,
      "end_time": 17650.0,
      "text": "He had seen it both times."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 17650.0,
      "end_time": 21600.0,
      "text": "Squinting toward the sky, he had seen the sleek jet, almost a blur at its high speed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 21600.0,
      "end_time": 24550.0,
      "text": "go past, and a second later heard the blast of sound that"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 24550.0,
      "end_time": 25550.0,
      "text": "followed."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 25550.0,
      "end_time": 27150.0,
      "text": "Then one more time, a moment later, from the opposite"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 27150.0,
      "end_time": 29130.0,
      "text": "direction, the same plane."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 29130.0,
      "end_time": 30520.0,
      "text": "At first, he had been only fascinated."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 30520.0,
      "end_time": 33390.0,
      "text": "He had never seen aircraft so close, for it was against the"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 33390.0,
      "end_time": 35820.0,
      "text": "rules for Pilots to fly over the community."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 35820.0,
      "end_time": 39079.0,
      "text": "Occasionally, when supplies were de- livered by cargo planes to the landing field"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 39079.0,
      "end_time": 41719.0,
      "text": "across the river, the children rode their bicycles to the riverbank"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 41719.0,
      "end_time": 44510.0,
      "text": "and watched, intrigued, the unloading and then the takeoff"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 44510.0,
      "end_time": 47980.0,
      "text": "directed to the west, always away from the community."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 47980.0,
      "end_time": 50480.0,
      "text": "But the aircraft a year ago had been different."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 50480.0,
      "end_time": 53319.0,
      "text": "It was not a squat, fat-bellied cargo plane but a needle-nosed"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 53319.0,
      "end_time": 54690.0,
      "text": "single-pilot jet."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 54690.0,
      "end_time": 57500.0,
      "text": "Jonas, looking around anxiously, had seen others — adults"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 57500.0,
      "end_time": 60420.0,
      "text": "as well as children — stop what they were doing and wait,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 60420.0,
      "end_time": 63239.0,
      "text": "confused, for an explanation of the frightening event."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 63239.0,
      "end_time": 65540.0,
      "text": "Then all of the citizens had been ordered to go into the"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 65540.0,
      "end_time": 68540.0,
      "text": "nearest building and stay there, immediately, the rasping"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 68540.0,
      "end_time": 71000.0,
      "text": "voice through the speakers had said, leave your bicy-"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 71000.0,
      "end_time": 72320.0,
      "text": "cles WHERE THEY ARE."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 72320.0,
      "end_time": 74860.0,
      "text": "Instantly, obediently, Jonas had dropped his bike on its"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 74860.0,
      "end_time": 77370.0,
      "text": "side on the path behind his family’s dwelling."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 77370.0,
      "end_time": 79750.0,
      "text": "He had run indoors and stayed there, alone."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 79750.0,
      "end_time": 81891.0,
      "text": "His parents were both at work, and his little sister, Lily, was at"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 81891.0,
      "end_time": 85160.0,
      "text": "the Childcare Center where she spent her after-school hours."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 85160.0,
      "end_time": 86750.0,
      "text": "Looking through the front window, he had seen no"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 86750.0,
      "end_time": 89450.0,
      "text": "people: none of the busy afternoon crew of Street Cleaners,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 89450.0,
      "end_time": 91960.0,
      "text": "Landscape Workers, and Food Delivery people who usually"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 91960.0,
      "end_time": 94520.0,
      "text": "populated the community at that time of day."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 94520.0,
      "end_time": 96680.0,
      "text": "He saw only the abandoned bikes here and there on their"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 96680.0,
      "end_time": 99490.0,
      "text": "sides; an upturned wheel on one was still revolving"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 99490.0,
      "end_time": 100560.0,
      "text": "slowly."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 100560.0,
      "end_time": 102030.0,
      "text": "He had been frightened then."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 102030.0,
      "end_time": 105950.0,
      "text": "The sense of his own community silent, waiting, had made his stomach"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 105950.0,
      "end_time": 106950.0,
      "text": "churn."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 106950.0,
      "end_time": 107950.0,
      "text": "He had trembled."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 107950.0,
      "end_time": 109070.0,
      "text": "But it had been nothing."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 109070.0,
      "end_time": 111810.0,
      "text": "Within minutes the speakers had crackled again, and the voice, reassuring"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 111810.0,
      "end_time": 115270.0,
      "text": "now and less urgent, had explained that a Pilot-in-Training"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 115270.0,
      "end_time": 117760.0,
      "text": "had misread his navigational instructions and made a wrong"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 117760.0,
      "end_time": 118760.0,
      "text": "turn."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 118760.0,
      "end_time": 120280.0,
      "text": "Des- perately the Pilot had been trying to make"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 120280.0,
      "end_time": 123110.0,
      "text": "his way back before his error was noticed."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 123110.0,
      "end_time": 125490.0,
      "text": "NEEDLESS TO SAY, HE WILL BE RELEASED, the Voice"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 125490.0,
      "end_time": 127330.0,
      "text": "had said, followed by silence."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 127330.0,
      "end_time": 130670.0,
      "text": "There was an ironic tone to that final message, as if the Speaker found"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 130669.99999999999,
      "end_time": 133349.0,
      "text": "it amusing; and Jonas had smiled a little, though he knew"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 133349.0,
      "end_time": 135400.0,
      "text": "what a grim statement it had been."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 135400.0,
      "end_time": 139019.0,
      "text": "For a contributing citizen to be re- leased from the community was a final decision,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 139019.0,
      "end_time": 143409.0,
      "text": "a terrible punishment, an overwhelming statement of failure."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 143409.0,
      "end_time": 145110.0,
      "text": "Even the children were scolded if they used the term"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 145110.0,
      "end_time": 147890.0,
      "text": "lightly at play, jeering at a teammate who missed a catch or"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 147890.0,
      "end_time": 149520.0,
      "text": "stumbled in a race."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 149520.0,
      "end_time": 152709.0,
      "text": "Jonas had done it once, had shouted at his best friend, “That’s it, Asher!"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 152709.0,
      "end_time": 155400.0,
      "text": "You’re released!” when Asher’s clumsy error had lost a match for"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 155400.0,
      "end_time": 156629.0,
      "text": "his team."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 156629.0,
      "end_time": 158849.0,
      "text": "He had been taken aside for a brief and serious talk"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 158849.0,
      "end_time": 161680.0,
      "text": "by the coach, had hung his head with guilt and embarrassment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 161680.0,
      "end_time": 164109.0,
      "text": "and apologized to Asher after the game."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 164109.0,
      "end_time": 166250.0,
      "text": "Now, thinking about the feeling of fear as he pedaled"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 166250.0,
      "end_time": 169170.0,
      "text": "home along the river path, he remembered that moment of"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 169170.0,
      "end_time": 171420.0,
      "text": "palpable, stomach-sinking terror when the aircraft had"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 171420.0,
      "end_time": 172760.0,
      "text": "streaked above."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 172760.0,
      "end_time": 175650.0,
      "text": "It was not what he was feeling now with December approaching."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 175650.0,
      "end_time": 178519.0,
      "text": "He searched for the right word to describe his own feeling."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 178519.0,
      "end_time": 179819.0,
      "text": "Jonas was careful about language."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 179819.0,
      "end_time": 182799.0,
      "text": "Not like his friend, Asher, who talked too fast and mixed things"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 182799.0,
      "end_time": 186040.0,
      "text": "up, scrambling words and phrases until they were barely recognizable"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 186040.0,
      "end_time": 188049.0,
      "text": "and often very funny."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 188049.0,
      "end_time": 189840.0,
      "text": "Jonas grinned, remembering the morning that Asher had"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 189840.0,
      "end_time": 193180.0,
      "text": "dashed into the classroom, late as usual, arriving"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 193180.0,
      "end_time": 195609.0,
      "text": "breathlessly in the middle of the chanting of the morning"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 195609.0,
      "end_time": 196609.0,
      "text": "anthem."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 196609.0,
      "end_time": 198620.0,
      "text": "When the class took their seats at the conclusion of"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 198620.0,
      "end_time": 201239.0,
      "text": "the patriotic hymn, Asher remained standing to make his"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 201239.0,
      "end_time": 203430.0,
      "text": "public apology as was required."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 203430.0,
      "end_time": 206660.0,
      "text": "“I apologize for inconveniencing my learning commu-"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 206660.0,
      "end_time": 207660.0,
      "text": "nity.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 207660.0,
      "end_time": 208900.0,
      "text": "Asher ran through the standard apology phrase rap-"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 208900.0,
      "end_time": 210579.0,
      "text": "idly, still catching his breath."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 210579.0,
      "end_time": 213510.0,
      "text": "The Instructor and class waited patiently for his explanation."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 213510.0,
      "end_time": 216510.0,
      "text": "The students had all been grinning, because they had listened to"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 216510.0,
      "end_time": 218579.0,
      "text": "Asher’s expla- nations so many times before."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 218579.0,
      "end_time": 222969.0,
      "text": "“I left home at the correct time but when I was riding along near the hatchery, the"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 222969.0,
      "end_time": 224150.0,
      "text": "crew was separating some salmon."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 224150.0,
      "end_time": 226909.0,
      "text": "1 guess I just got distraught, watching them."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 226909.0,
      "end_time": 229870.0,
      "text": "“I apologize to my classmates,” Asher concluded."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 229870.0,
      "end_time": 232010.0,
      "text": "He smoothed his rumpled tunic and sat down."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 232010.0,
      "end_time": 234519.0,
      "text": "“We accept your apology, Asher.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 234519.0,
      "end_time": 237889.0,
      "text": "The class recited the standard response in unison."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 237889.0,
      "end_time": 240510.0,
      "text": "Many of the students were biting their lips to keep from laughing."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 240510.0,
      "end_time": 243499.0,
      "text": "“I accept your apology, Asher,” the Instructor said."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 243499.0,
      "end_time": 244499.0,
      "text": "He was smiling."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 244499.0,
      "end_time": 248060.0,
      "text": "“And I thank you, because once again you have provided an opportunity for a lesson"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 248060.0,
      "end_time": 249269.0,
      "text": "in language."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 249269.0,
      "end_time": 251909.0,
      "text": "‘Distraught’ is too strong an adjective to describe salmon-"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 251909.0,
      "end_time": 252909.0,
      "text": "viewing.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 252909.0,
      "end_time": 253959.0,
      "text": "He turned and wrote “distraught” on the in-"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 253959.0,
      "end_time": 255309.0,
      "text": "structional board."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 255309.0,
      "end_time": 256930.0,
      "text": "Beside it he wrote “distracted.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 256930.0,
      "end_time": 260299.0,
      "text": "Jonas, nearing his home now, smiled at the recollection."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 260298.99999999997,
      "end_time": 262759.0,
      "text": "Thinking, still, as he wheeled his bike into its narrow port"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 262759.0,
      "end_time": 265860.0,
      "text": "beside the door, he realized that frightened was the wrong"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 265860.0,
      "end_time": 268379.0,
      "text": "word to describe his feelings, now that December was al-"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 268379.0,
      "end_time": 269379.0,
      "text": "most here."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 269379.0,
      "end_time": 270949.0,
      "text": "It was too strong an adjective."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 270949.0,
      "end_time": 273410.0,
      "text": "He had waited a long time for this special December."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 273410.0,
      "end_time": 276011.0,
      "text": "Now that it was almost upon him, he wasn’t frightened, but"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 276011.0,
      "end_time": 278349.0,
      "text": "he was . . . eager, he decided."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 278349.0,
      "end_time": 279669.0,
      "text": "He was eager for it to come."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 279669.0,
      "end_time": 281599.0,
      "text": "And he was excited, certainly."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 281599.0,
      "end_time": 283960.0,
      "text": "All of the Elevens were excited about the event that would be coming"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 283960.0,
      "end_time": 285250.0,
      "text": "so soon."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 285250.0,
      "end_time": 287009.0,
      "text": "But there was a little shudder of nervousness when he"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 287009.0,
      "end_time": 289370.0,
      "text": "thought about it, about what might happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 289370.0,
      "end_time": 290949.0,
      "text": "Apprehensive, Jonas decided."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 290949.0,
      "end_time": 292530.0,
      "text": "That’s what I am."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 292530.0,
      "end_time": 295050.0,
      "text": "“Who wants to be the first tonight, for feelings?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 295050.0,
      "end_time": 297380.0,
      "text": "Jonas’s father asked, at the conclusion of their evening"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 297380.0,
      "end_time": 298380.0,
      "text": "meal."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 298380.0,
      "end_time": 301139.0,
      "text": "It was one of the rituals, the evening telling of feelings."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 301139.0,
      "end_time": 303470.0,
      "text": "Sometimes Jonas and his sister, Lily, argued over turns,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 303470.0,
      "end_time": 304659.0,
      "text": "over who would get to go first."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 304659.0,
      "end_time": 307840.0,
      "text": "Their parents, of course, were part of the ritual; they, too, told their"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 307840.0,
      "end_time": 309140.0,
      "text": "feelings each evening."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 309140.0,
      "end_time": 311610.0,
      "text": "But like all parents — all adults — they didn’t"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 311610.0,
      "end_time": 313479.0,
      "text": "fight and wheedle for their turn."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 313479.0,
      "end_time": 314770.0,
      "text": "Nor did Jonas, tonight."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 314770.0,
      "end_time": 317030.0,
      "text": "His feelings were too compli- cated this evening."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 317030.0,
      "end_time": 320060.0,
      "text": "He wanted to share them, but he wasn’t eager to begin the process of sifting through"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 320060.0,
      "end_time": 322850.0,
      "text": "his own complicated emotions, even with the help that"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 322850.0,
      "end_time": 324540.0,
      "text": "he knew his parents could give."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 324540.0,
      "end_time": 327180.0,
      "text": "“You go, Lily,” he said, seeing his sister, who was much"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 327180.0,
      "end_time": 330190.0,
      "text": "younger — only a Seven — wiggling with impatience in"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 330190.0,
      "end_time": 331190.0,
      "text": "her chair."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 331190.0,
      "end_time": 333750.0,
      "text": "“I felt very angry this afternoon,” Lily announced."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 333750.0,
      "end_time": 335409.0,
      "text": "“My Childcare group was at the play area, and"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 335409.0,
      "end_time": 337990.0,
      "text": "we had a visiting group of Sevens, and they didn’t obey the"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 337990.0,
      "end_time": 339730.0,
      "text": "rules at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 339730.0,
      "end_time": 341550.0,
      "text": "One of them — a male; I don’t know his name"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 341550.0,
      "end_time": 344200.0,
      "text": "— kept going right to the front of the line for the slide,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 344200.0,
      "end_time": 345759.0,
      "text": "even though the rest of us were all waiting."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 345759.0,
      "end_time": 347460.0,
      "text": "I felt so angry at him."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 347460.0,
      "end_time": 350169.0,
      "text": "I made my hand into a fist, like this.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 350169.0,
      "end_time": 352690.0,
      "text": "She held up a clenched fist and the rest of the family smiled at her small"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 352690.0,
      "end_time": 353720.0,
      "text": "defiant gesture."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 353720.0,
      "end_time": 356740.0,
      "text": "“Why do you think the visitors didn’t obey the rules?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 356740.0,
      "end_time": 357870.0,
      "text": "Mother asked."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 357870.0,
      "end_time": 359150.0,
      "text": "Lily considered, and shook her head."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 359150.0,
      "end_time": 360150.0,
      "text": "“I don’t know."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 360150.0,
      "end_time": 361610.0,
      "text": "They acted like . . . like ...”"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 361610.0,
      "end_time": 363020.0,
      "text": "“Animals?” Jonas suggested."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 363020.0,
      "end_time": 364020.0,
      "text": "He laughed."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 364020.0,
      "end_time": 366780.0,
      "text": "“That’s right,” Lily said, laughing too."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 366780.0,
      "end_time": 368229.0,
      "text": "“Like animals.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 368229.0,
      "end_time": 370260.0,
      "text": "Neither child knew what the word meant, exactly, but it"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 370260.0,
      "end_time": 373530.0,
      "text": "was often used to describe someone uneducated or clumsy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 373530.0,
      "end_time": 375020.0,
      "text": "someone who didn’t fit in."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 375020.0,
      "end_time": 376550.0,
      "text": "“Where were the visitors from?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 376550.0,
      "end_time": 377550.0,
      "text": "Father asked."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 377550.0,
      "end_time": 378830.0,
      "text": "Lily frowned, trying to remember."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 378830.0,
      "end_time": 381960.0,
      "text": "“Our leader told us, when he made the welcome speech, but I can’t"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 381960.0,
      "end_time": 382960.0,
      "text": "remember."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 382960.0,
      "end_time": 383960.0,
      "text": "I guess I wasn’t paying attention."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 383960.0,
      "end_time": 384960.0,
      "text": "It was from another community."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 384960.0,
      "end_time": 387520.0,
      "text": "They had to leave very early, and they had their midday meal on the bus.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 387520.0,
      "end_time": 388520.0,
      "text": "Mother nodded."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 388520.0,
      "end_time": 391220.0,
      "text": "“Do you think it’s possible that their rules may be different?"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 391220.0,
      "end_time": 394919.0,
      "text": "And so they simply didn’t know what your play area rules were?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 394919.0,
      "end_time": 396461.0,
      "text": "Lily shrugged, and nodded."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 396461.0,
      "end_time": 397461.0,
      "text": "“I suppose.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 397461.0,
      "end_time": 399669.0,
      "text": "“You’ve visited other communities, haven’t you?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 399669.0,
      "end_time": 400669.0,
      "text": "Jonas asked."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 400669.0,
      "end_time": 402009.0,
      "text": "“My group has, often.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 402009.0,
      "end_time": 403009.0,
      "text": "Lily nodded again."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 403009.0,
      "end_time": 405789.0,
      "text": "“When we were Sixes, we went and shared a whole school day with a group of"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 405789.0,
      "end_time": 407310.0,
      "text": "Sixes in their community.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 407310.0,
      "end_time": 409430.0,
      "text": "“How did you feel when you were there?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 409430.0,
      "end_time": 410430.0,
      "text": "Lily frowned."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 410430.0,
      "end_time": 411720.0,
      "text": "“I felt strange."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 411720.0,
      "end_time": 413210.0,
      "text": "Because their methods were different."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 413210.0,
      "end_time": 417229.0,
      "text": "They were learning usages that my group hadn’t learned yet, so we felt stupid.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 417229.0,
      "end_time": 418569.0,
      "text": "Father was listening with interest."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 418569.0,
      "end_time": 421330.0,
      "text": "“I’m thinking, Lily,” he said, “about the boy who didn’t obey"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 421330.0,
      "end_time": 422330.0,
      "text": "the rules today."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 422330.0,
      "end_time": 424820.0,
      "text": "Do you think it’s possible that he felt strange and stupid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 424820.0,
      "end_time": 427410.0,
      "text": "being in a new place with rules that he didn’t know"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 427410.0,
      "end_time": 428410.0,
      "text": "about?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 428410.0,
      "end_time": 429620.0,
      "text": "Lily pondered that."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 429620.0,
      "end_time": 431719.0,
      "text": "“Yes,” she said, finally."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 431719.0,
      "end_time": 435160.0,
      "text": "“I feel a little sorry for him,” Jonas said, “even though I"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 435160.0,
      "end_time": 436160.0,
      "text": "don’t even know him."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 436160.0,
      "end_time": 439750.0,
      "text": "I feel sorry for anyone who is in a place where he feels strange and stupid.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 439750.0,
      "end_time": 441680.0,
      "text": "“How do you feel now, Lily?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 441680.0,
      "end_time": 442680.0,
      "text": "Father asked."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 442680.0,
      "end_time": 443680.0,
      "text": "“Still angry?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 443680.0,
      "end_time": 445199.0,
      "text": "“I guess not,” Lily decided."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 445199.0,
      "end_time": 447550.0,
      "text": "“I guess I feel a little sorry for him."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 447550.0,
      "end_time": 449090.0,
      "text": "And sorry I made a fist.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 449090.0,
      "end_time": 450319.0,
      "text": "She grinned."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 450319.0,
      "end_time": 451990.0,
      "text": "Jonas smiled back at his sister."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 451990.0,
      "end_time": 455000.0,
      "text": "Lily’s feelings were always straightforward, fairly simple, usually"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 455000.0,
      "end_time": 456280.0,
      "text": "easy to re- solve."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 456280.0,
      "end_time": 458039.0,
      "text": "He guessed that his own had been, too, when he was"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 458039.0,
      "end_time": 459039.0,
      "text": "a Seven."
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 459039.0,
      "end_time": 461270.0,
      "text": "He listened politely, though not very attentively, while"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 461270.0,
      "end_time": 464259.0,
      "text": "his father took his turn, describing a feeling of worry that"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 464259.0,
      "end_time": 467879.0,
      "text": "he’d had that day at work: a concern about one of the"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 467879.0,
      "end_time": 469880.0,
      "text": "newchildren who wasn’t doing well."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 469880.0,
      "end_time": 472139.0,
      "text": "Jonas’s father’s title was Nurturer."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 472139.0,
      "end_time": 475210.0,
      "text": "He and the other Nurturers were responsible for all the physical and emotional needs of"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 475210.0,
      "end_time": 477389.0,
      "text": "every new-child during its earliest life."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 477389.0,
      "end_time": 481530.0,
      "text": "It was a very important job, Jonas knew, but it wasn’t one that interested"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 481530.0,
      "end_time": 482530.0,
      "text": "him much."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 482530.0,
      "end_time": 483530.0,
      "text": "“What gender is it?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 483530.0,
      "end_time": 484530.0,
      "text": "Lily asked."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 484530.0,
      "end_time": 485530.0,
      "text": "“Male,” Father said."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 485530.0,
      "end_time": 487310.0,
      "text": "“He’s a sweet little male with a lovely disposition."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 487310.0,
      "end_time": 491129.0,
      "text": "But he isn’t growing as fast as he should, and he doesn’t sleep soundly."
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 491129.0,
      "end_time": 494960.0,
      "text": "We have him in the extra care section for supplementary nurturing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 494960.0,
      "end_time": 497120.0,
      "text": "but the committee’s beginning to talk about releasing"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 497120.0,
      "end_time": 498120.0,
      "text": "him.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 498120.0,
      "end_time": 500169.0,
      "text": "“Oh, no, ” Mother murmured sympathetically."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 500169.0,
      "end_time": 503100.0,
      "text": "“I know how sad that must make you feel.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 503100.0,
      "end_time": 505780.0,
      "text": "Jonas and Lily both nodded sympathetically as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 505780.0,
      "end_time": 507690.0,
      "text": "Release of newchildren was always sad, because they"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 507690.0,
      "end_time": 510310.0,
      "text": "hadn’t had a chance to enjoy life within the community yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 510310.0,
      "end_time": 512280.0,
      "text": "And they hadn’t done anything wrong."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 512280.0,
      "end_time": 514940.0,
      "text": "There were only two occasions of release which were not"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 514940.00000000006,
      "end_time": 516050.00000000006,
      "text": "punishment."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 516049.99999999994,
      "end_time": 520168.99999999994,
      "text": "Release of the elderly, which was a time of celebration for a life well and fully lived;"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 520169.0,
      "end_time": 522209.0,
      "text": "and release of a newchild, which always brought a sense of"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 522208.99999999994,
      "end_time": 523208.99999999994,
      "text": "what-could-we- have-done."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 523208.99999999994,
      "end_time": 527950.0,
      "text": "This was especially troubling for the Nurturers, like Father, who felt they had failed somehow."
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 527950.0,
      "end_time": 529630.0,
      "text": "But it happened very rarely."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 529630.0,
      "end_time": 531730.0,
      "text": "“Well,” Father said, “I’m going to keep trying."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 531730.0,
      "end_time": 534810.0,
      "text": "I may ask the committee for permission to bring him here at night,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 534810.0,
      "end_time": 535810.0,
      "text": "if you don’t mind."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 535810.0,
      "end_time": 537450.0,
      "text": "You know what the night-crew Nurturers are like."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 537450.0,
      "end_time": 539810.0,
      "text": "1 think this little guy needs something extra.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 539810.0,
      "end_time": 542279.0,
      "text": "“Of course,” Mother said, and Jonas and Lily nodded."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 542279.0,
      "end_time": 544740.0,
      "text": "They had heard Father complain about the night crew be-"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 544740.0,
      "end_time": 545740.0,
      "text": "fore."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 545740.0,
      "end_time": 547790.0,
      "text": "It was a lesser job, night-crew nurturing, assigned to"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 547790.0,
      "end_time": 549870.0,
      "text": "those who lacked the interest or skills or insight for the"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 549870.0,
      "end_time": 552500.0,
      "text": "more vital jobs of the daytime hours."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 552500.0,
      "end_time": 554830.0,
      "text": "Most of the people on the night crew had not even been given spouses"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 554830.0,
      "end_time": 557339.0,
      "text": "because they lacked, somehow, the essential capacity"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 557339.0,
      "end_time": 560149.0,
      "text": "to connect to others, which was required for the creation"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 560149.0,
      "end_time": 561209.0,
      "text": "of a family unit."
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 561209.0,
      "end_time": 565720.0,
      "text": "“Maybe we could even keep him,” Lily suggested sweetly, trying to look innocent."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 565720.0,
      "end_time": 569110.0,
      "text": "The look was fake, Jonas knew; they all knew."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 569110.0,
      "end_time": 572140.0,
      "text": "“Lily,” Mother reminded her, smiling, “you know the"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 572140.0,
      "end_time": 573140.0,
      "text": "rules.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 573140.0,
      "end_time": 575950.0,
      "text": "Two children — one male, one female — to each family"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 575950.0,
      "end_time": 576950.0,
      "text": "unit."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 576950.0,
      "end_time": 579860.0,
      "text": "It was written very clearly in the rules."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 579860.0,
      "end_time": 580860.0,
      "text": "Lily giggled."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 580860.0,
      "end_time": 582660.0,
      "text": "“Well,” she said, “I thought maybe just this"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 582660.0,
      "end_time": 583660.0,
      "text": "once.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 583660.0,
      "end_time": 585800.0,
      "text": "Next, Mother, who held a prominent position at the De-"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 585800.0,
      "end_time": 588300.0,
      "text": "partment of Justice, talked about her feelings."
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 588300.0,
      "end_time": 591930.0,
      "text": "Today a re- peat offender had been brought before her,"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 591930.0,
      "end_time": 594070.0,
      "text": "someone who had broken the rules before."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 594070.0,
      "end_time": 596941.0,
      "text": "Someone who she hoped had been adequately and fairly punished, and who"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 596941.0,
      "end_time": 599459.0,
      "text": "had been restored to his place: to his job, his home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 599459.0,
      "end_time": 600480.0,
      "text": "his family unit."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 600480.0,
      "end_time": 602880.0,
      "text": "To see him brought before her a second time caused her"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 602880.0,
      "end_time": 605430.0,
      "text": "overwhelming feelings of frustration and anger."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 605430.0,
      "end_time": 606430.0,
      "text": "And even"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 606430.0,
      "end_time": 608529.0,
      "text": "guilt, that she hadn’t made a difference in his life."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 608529.0,
      "end_time": 611070.0,
      "text": "“I feel frightened, too, for him,” she confessed."
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 611070.0,
      "end_time": 613230.0,
      "text": "“You know that there’s no third chance."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 613230.0,
      "end_time": 615470.0,
      "text": "The rules say that if there’s a third transgression, he simply"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 615470.0,
      "end_time": 616829.0,
      "text": "has to be released.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 616829.0,
      "end_time": 618269.0,
      "text": "Jonas shivered."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 618269.0,
      "end_time": 619269.0,
      "text": "He knew it happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 619269.0,
      "end_time": 622079.0,
      "text": "There was even a boy in his group of Elevens whose father had been"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 622079.0,
      "end_time": 623860.0,
      "text": "released years before."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 623860.0,
      "end_time": 626230.0,
      "text": "No one ever mentioned it; the disgrace was unspeakable."
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 626230.0,
      "end_time": 628680.0,
      "text": "It was hard to imagine."
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 628680.0,
      "end_time": 630260.0,
      "text": "Lily stood up and went to her mother."
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 630260.0,
      "end_time": 631560.0,
      "text": "She stroked her mother’s arm."
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 631560.0,
      "end_time": 634279.0,
      "text": "From his place at the table, Father reached over and took"
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 634279.0,
      "end_time": 635279.0,
      "text": "her hand."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 635279.0,
      "end_time": 636440.0,
      "text": "Jonas reached for the other."
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 636440.0,
      "end_time": 638079.0,
      "text": "One by one, they comforted her."
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 638079.0,
      "end_time": 641890.0,
      "text": "Soon she smiled, thanked them, and murmured that she felt soothed."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 641890.0,
      "end_time": 643320.0,
      "text": "The ritual continued."
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 643320.0,
      "end_time": 644320.0,
      "text": "“Jonas?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 644320.0,
      "end_time": 645320.0,
      "text": "Father asked."
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 645320.0,
      "end_time": 646430.0,
      "text": "“You’re last, tonight.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 646430.0,
      "end_time": 647430.0,
      "text": "Jonas sighed."
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 647430.0,
      "end_time": 650270.0,
      "text": "This evening he almost would have pre- ferred to keep his feelings hidden."
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 650270.0,
      "end_time": 653400.0,
      "text": "But it was, of course, against the rules."
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 653400.0,
      "end_time": 656139.0,
      "text": "“I’m feeling apprehensive,” he confessed, glad that the"
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 656139.0,
      "end_time": 659310.0,
      "text": "appropriate descriptive word had finally come to him."
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 659310.0,
      "end_time": 660860.0,
      "text": "“Why is that, son?”"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 660860.0,
      "end_time": 661990.0,
      "text": "His father looked concerned."
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 661990.0,
      "end_time": 665350.0,
      "text": "“I know there’s really nothing to worry about,” Jonas"
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 665350.0,
      "end_time": 667550.0,
      "text": "explained, “and that every adult has been through it."
    },
    {
      "index": 314,
      "start_time": 667550.0,
      "end_time": 670269.0,
      "text": "I know you have, Father, and you too, Mother."
    },
    {
      "index": 315,
      "start_time": 670269.0,
      "end_time": 672630.0,
      "text": "But it’s the Ceremony that I’m apprehensive about."
    },
    {
      "index": 316,
      "start_time": 672630.0,
      "end_time": 674760.0,
      "text": "It’s almost De- cember.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 317,
      "start_time": 674760.0,
      "end_time": 676220.0,
      "text": "Lily looked up, her eyes wide."
    },
    {
      "index": 318,
      "start_time": 676220.0,
      "end_time": 680090.0,
      "text": "“The Ceremony of Twelve,” she whispered in an awed voice."
    },
    {
      "index": 319,
      "start_time": 680090.0,
      "end_time": 682160.0,
      "text": "Even the small- est children — Lily’s age and younger"
    },
    {
      "index": 320,
      "start_time": 682160.0,
      "end_time": 684810.0,
      "text": "— knew that it lay in the future for each of them."
    },
    {
      "index": 321,
      "start_time": 684810.0,
      "end_time": 687850.0,
      "text": "“I’m glad you told us of your feelings,” Father said."
    },
    {
      "index": 322,
      "start_time": 687850.0,
      "end_time": 690649.0,
      "text": "“Lily,” Mother said, beckoning to the little girl, “Go on"
    },
    {
      "index": 323,
      "start_time": 690649.0,
      "end_time": 692269.0,
      "text": "now and get into your nightclothes."
    },
    {
      "index": 324,
      "start_time": 692269.0,
      "end_time": 695420.0,
      "text": "Father and I are going to stay here and talk to Jonas for a while.”"
    },
    {
      "index": 325,
      "start_time": 695420.0,
      "end_time": 698480.0,
      "text": "Lily sighed, but obediently she got down from her chair."
    },
    {
      "index": 326,
      "start_time": 698480.0,
      "end_time": 700040.0,
      "text": "“Privately?” she asked."
    },
    {
      "index": 327,
      "start_time": 700040.0,
      "end_time": 701040.0,
      "text": "Mother nodded."
    },
    {
      "index": 328,
      "start_time": 701040.0,
      "end_time": 703279.0,
      "text": "“Yes,” she said, “this talk will be a"
    },
    {
      "index": 329,
      "start_time": 703279.0,
      "end_time": 713279.0,
      "text": "private one with Jonas.”"
    }
  ]
}